article.headline: La Salle 76, Richmond 67
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Rodney Green and Darnell Harris each scored five points during a 20-10 late-game rally on Saturday to lead La Salle to a 76-67 win over Richmond. The Spiders (9-8, 2-2 Atlantic 10) had taken a 57-56 lead on Gaston Moliva's layup with 6:10 remaining before Jerrell Williams hit a layup to start the La Salle spurt. The Explorers (7-9, 2-1) led by as many as 11 down the stretch. La Salle led by as many as 12 in the first, following a 20-8 run with 3:30 remaining and led 38-31 at the half. Harris finished with 24 points for the Explorers, Green added 16 and Ruben Guillandeaux 12. David Gonzalvez led the Spiders with 21 points, Kevin Smith added 12 and Dan Geriot had 11.
